undational condition of modern Irish political identity, Terror and Irish Modernism provides a thoroughly new genealogy of modern Irish fiction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish fictionxIrish authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aGothic fiction (Literary genre), EnglishzIrelandxHistory and criticism. 0aGothic revival (Literature)zIreland. 0aModernism (Literature)zIreland. 0aTerror in literature. 4aArea Studies : British Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Postcolonial Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aLiterature : Literary History. 4aLiterature : Nineteenth-Century Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143842834540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438428345423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438428345/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles